	<H1>Matching Questions:</H1>


	<P>Match the terms on the left with the definition in the column on the right. Enter the <B>lowercase</B> letter of that definition in the box to the left of the question number.<BR><BR>


	<TABLE CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=2 BORDER=0>


	<TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN=TOP><H2><INPUT TYPE=TEXT NAME="Q15_1" SIZE=3></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH="35%"><H2>1. balance of payments</TD><TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH="55%"><P>a. the change in a nation's foreign assets minus foreign liabilities</TD></TR>


	<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2><INPUT TYPE=TEXT NAME="Q15_2" SIZE=3></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2>2. capital inflow</TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><P>b. net credits minus net debits on merchandise</TD></TR>


	<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2><INPUT TYPE=TEXT NAME="Q15_3" SIZE=3></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2>3. merchandise trade balance</TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><P>c. a systematic account of all the exchanges of value between residents of a country and the rest of the world during a given period of time.</TD></TR>


	<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2><INPUT TYPE=TEXT NAME="Q15_4" SIZE=3></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2>4. official international reserves</TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><P>d. the sum of the current account balance plus the private capital account balance</TD></TR>


	<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2><INPUT TYPE=TEXT NAME="Q15_5" SIZE=3></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2>5. capital outflow</TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><P>e. net exports of goods and services.</TD></TR>


	<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2><INPUT TYPE=TEXT NAME="Q15_6" SIZE=3></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2>6. goods and services balance</TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><P>f. net credits minus debits on the flows of goods, services, income, and unilateral transfers.</TD></TR>


	<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2><INPUT TYPE=TEXT NAME="Q15_7" SIZE=3></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2>7. goods, services, and income balance</TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><P>g. money like assets such as gold that are generally recognized as official assets</TD></TR>


	<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2><INPUT TYPE=TEXT NAME="Q15_8" SIZE=3></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2>8. current account balance</TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><P>h. an increase in a nation's liabilities to foreign residents or a decrease in assets previously obtained from other countries.</TD></TR>


	<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2><INPUT TYPE=TEXT NAME="Q15_9" SIZE=3></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2>9. capital account balance</TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><P>i. an increase in a nation's assets obtained from other countries or a decrease in its liabilities to other countries.</TD></TR>


	<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2><INPUT TYPE=TEXT NAME="Q15_10" SIZE=3></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2>10. direct investments</TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><P>j. net credits minus debits involving changes in private national residents' foreign financial assets and liabilities.</TD></TR>


	<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2><INPUT TYPE=TEXT NAME="Q15_11" SIZE=3></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2>11. net foreign investment</TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><P>k. net income flows and net exports of goods and services.</TD></TR>


	<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2><INPUT TYPE=TEXT NAME="Q15_12" SIZE=3></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2>12. official settlements balance</TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><P>l. any flow of lending to, or purchases of ownership in, a foreign enterprise that is largely owned by residents of the investing country.</TD></TR>


	<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2><INPUT TYPE=TEXT NAME="Q15_13" SIZE=3></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2>13. international investment position</TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><P>m. the net accumulation of foreign assets minus foreign liabilities.</TD></TR>


	</TABLE>


